/-- Average value of a function `f` w.r.t. a measure `μ`, notation: `⨍ x, f x ∂μ`. It is defined as
`(μ univ).toReal⁻¹ • ∫ x, f x ∂μ`, so it is equal to zero if `f` is not integrable or if `μ` is an
